headline: Apple, Gen Z on personal finance: Wealth
summary: From trending tickers to how Gen Z is shaping the future of personal finance, Friday’s edition of Wealth! is here with the rundown.With Super Micro Computer (SMCI) facing a potential delisting from the Nasdaq, Yahoo Finance's Rachelle Akuffo explains what this means for shareholders and how to navigate over-the-counter markets (OTC). RBC gives Starbucks (SBUX) and Chipotle (CMG) an outperform rating, with price targets of $115 and $70, respectively.Finally, Apple (AAPL) could see a $256 increase in iPhone production costs if President-elect Trump's proposed China tariffs are enacted, according to Jefferies analyst Edison Lee.For more expert insight and the latest market action, click here. This post was written by Cindy Mizaku.

headline: Starbucks, Chipotle could see 15% upside: RBC
summary: RBC has initiated coverage on Starbucks (SBUX) and Chipotle (CMG), giving both stocks an Outperform rating. Starbucks was given a $115 price target, with analyst Logan Reich citing growth potential and margin improvement in 2025 and 2026. Chipotle was assigned a $70 price target by Reich, with potential for unit growth and other catalysts justifying the valuation. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Wealth here. This post was written by Kevin Hall

headline: Starbucks wants to reclaim its coffeehouse crown. It won't be easy
summary: Starbucks (SBUX) is embarking on a bold turnaround plan under new CEO Brian Niccol. The coffee giant hopes to reclaim its coffeehouse crown by focusing on speed, service, and operational efficiency. Whether these sweeping changes will be enough to turn the tide remains a point of debate among experts.
